data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
Enter a nearby address into the box above and hit Search.
Right Click and drag to move around the map.
Left click the boundaries of your map to enclose the desired properties within a box.
Press delete to start drawing the boundaries again.
All properties found within the drawn box will automatically be filled in as homes once the map is locked.
When you are happy with your Map Scope, click the LOCK button.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
Left click a gray property to select it as a home on the map.
Left click on a home to reset it back to a gray property
Right click a home to turn it into a DNC.
Delete the house number from the list below to revert it back to regular home.
After you have finished marking your map move onto the Directions page.

data.name: lblDirectionsInstructions.Text
data.value:
The From field defaults to the Kingdom Hall address specified in your settings.
Enter a destination address in the To box and click Get Directions.
The turn by turn directions will be automatically entered into the box above.
You can enter custom directions if you wish.
Once you're finished proceed to the Export page.
